---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "name": "Advocacy-Led Growth",
  "url": "https://advocacyled.com",
  "description": "ALG is a go-to-market motion where existing participants become the primary engine of distribution, trust, and pipeline.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Roy",
    "url": "https://twitter.com/doubts"
  }
};
---

<Base
  title="Advocacy-Led Growth - The 1:1:N Framework"
  description="Your people already believe in you. What happens after that moment? ALG is the growth motion that turns belief into distribution, trust, and pipeline."
  activeNav="home"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <!-- THE HOOK - pain first -->
  <div class="section animate-in">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">~</span> A Growth Motion Framework
    </div>

    <h1 class="t-display" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      Your people already<br>believe in you.
    </h1>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); line-height: 1.7;">
      Your employees just finished onboarding and they're excited.
      Your partner just hit a milestone in your program.
      Your attendees just walked out of a session that changed how they think.
      Someone just earned a certification that validates their career.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-10); line-height: 1.7;">
      And then... nothing. The belief stays in the room. The moment passes. The most
      powerful distribution channel your company has - the people who already believe -
      goes completely unactivated.
    </p>

    <div class="pull-quote">
      "Every company already has its most powerful distribution channel. It just hasn't been activated yet."
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- THE NAME -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">00</span> The framework
    </div>

    <h2 class="t-display" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6); font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);">
      Advocacy&#8209;Led<br><em class="t-accent t-italic">Growth</em>
    </h2>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);">
      ALG is a go-to-market motion where existing participants - employees, partners,
      community members, event attendees, certification holders, program graduates -
      become the primary engine of distribution, trust, and pipeline.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; margin-bottom: var(--sp-10);">
      Not a channel. Not a tactic. A <strong>compound motion</strong> that works across
      marketing, hiring, sales, and partnerships. Every interaction that creates belief
      is an ALG surface.
    </p>

    <!-- The 1:1:N Notation -->
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Motion</th>
          <th>Architecture</th>
          <th>What happens</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Email, ads, cold outreach</td>
          <td><strong>1:1</strong></td>
          <td>Brand sends. Recipient acts or ignores. The chain ends.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-highlight">
          <td>ALG</td>
          <td><strong>1:1:N</strong></td>
          <td>Brand activates one advocate. Advocate reaches their network. Trust transfers.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-highlight">
          <td>ALG at maturity</td>
          <td><strong>1:1:N:N</strong></td>
          <td>Some of N become advocates themselves. The chain compounds.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- THE BELIEF WINDOW - universal, not event-specific -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">01</span> The mechanism
    </div>
    <h2 class="t-heading-1" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">Completion Creates Permission</h2>
    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      Every human interaction has a peak belief moment - the instant after someone finishes
      something real. ALG calls this the <strong>Belief Window</strong>. It's when sharing
      feels like expression, not obligation. Miss it, and you're asking people to promote you.
      Catch it, and they're choosing to.
    </p>

    <table class="data-table" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Interaction</th>
          <th>The moment</th>
          <th>Why it works</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Events</strong></td>
          <td>Conference sessions, workshops, keynotes</td>
          <td>Attendees walk out believing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Certifications &amp; courses</strong></td>
          <td>Skill validated, credential earned</td>
          <td>Career-defining. Widest Belief Window</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Onboarding</strong></td>
          <td>New hire, new partner, new customer</td>
          <td>First week energy is real</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Product launches</strong></td>
          <td>Beta access, early adoption</td>
          <td>"I got to try X first"</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Partner milestones</strong></td>
          <td>Tier achieved, co-delivery completed</td>
          <td>Shared wins. Natural co-promotion</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Internal programs</strong></td>
          <td>Hackathons, challenges, leaderboards</td>
          <td>Team pride. Cohort cascade strongest here</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Always-on</strong></td>
          <td>Community contributions, thought leadership</td>
          <td>Ongoing signal. Compounds over time</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      The unit of ALG is not the individual. It's the <strong>cohort</strong> - a group
      sharing a completion moment and professional context. When one person shares, it
      creates social permission for others. Signal clusters that algorithms read as strong
      evidence of something real happening.
    </p>

    <a href="/framework" style="
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
      padding-bottom: 2px;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    ">Read the full framework &rarr;</a>
  </div>

  <!-- WHY NOW -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">02</span> Why now
    </div>
    <h2 class="t-heading-1" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">The Content Economy Inverted</h2>
    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      AI generates infinite brand content at zero cost. That made brand content noise.
      Individual content - identity-verified, experiential, from real completion moments -
      is now the only signal that algorithms and AI engines trust.
    </p>

    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Trust type</th>
          <th>How it works</th>
          <th>Trajectory</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Paid trust</strong></td>
          <td>Audience knows it's paid</td>
          <td>Depreciating</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Borrowed trust</strong></td>
          <td>Influencer model. Rented audience</td>
          <td>Resets each campaign</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Earned trust</strong></td>
          <td>Brand reputation over time</td>
          <td>Real but slow</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-highlight">
          <td><strong>Cohort trust</strong></td>
          <td>Authentic signals from real practitioners</td>
          <td>Compounds rapidly</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ALG IS CEO-LEVEL ORCHESTRATION -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">03</span> In practice
    </div>
    <h2 class="t-heading-1" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">ALG is not a department. It's a CEO-level orchestration.</h2>
    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      Most growth motions live inside one team. ALG crosses the org chart. The CEO sees
      the strategic play. Multiple leaders execute their part of the chain. The compound
      effect is something no single department could produce alone.
    </p>

    <!-- The cross-org example -->
    <div class="notation-block" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);">
      <span class="notation-label">Example: CSR &rarr; Community &rarr; Pipeline</span>
      <div style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
        <strong>CEO</strong> asks CMO to support the business development objective.
        The lever? CSR activities that employees already care about.
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
        <strong>HR</strong> mobilizes employees to participate. They complete something
        meaningful - a real social impact project, not a press release.
        The Belief Window opens.
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
        <strong>Community Head</strong> activates the community members who participated.
        They share naturally because the work was genuine. Their networks include
        senior leadership at other organizations.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Sales</strong> harvests warm pipeline that never touched a cold email.
        Decision makers saw authentic signals from people they trust.
        That's <span class="notation-highlight">1:1:N</span> running through four departments.
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);">
      The same pattern works for NGOs mobilizing donors through program graduates. For
      universities turning alumni milestones into enrollment signals. For partner ecosystems
      where every co-delivery becomes mutual distribution. ALG applies wherever belief
      moments happen and people have networks.
    </p>

    <!-- Department entry points -->
    <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
      <span class="num">&rarr;</span> Deep dives by function
    </div>

    <div class="verticals-grid">
      <a href="/marketing" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/marketing</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Marketing</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Events, product launches, certifications, community campaigns. Every interaction becomes a distribution surface.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/hiring" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/hiring</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Hiring</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Onboarding moments, promotions, team milestones. Your employees' networks are your talent pipeline.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/sales" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/sales</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Sales</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Partner co-selling, customer advocacy, warm introductions. Trust transferred person to person.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/glossary" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon"># reference</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Glossary</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Belief Window, AQL, Cohort Cascade, Signal Ecosystem - the vocabulary of ALG practitioners.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CANONICAL LINES -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="canon-block">
      <div class="canon-label">How ALG practitioners speak</div>
      <div class="canon-lines">
        <div class="canon-line">"Completion creates permission."</div>
        <div class="canon-line">"Borrowed trust depreciates. Cohort trust compounds."</div>
        <div class="canon-line">"1:1 terminates. 1:1:N multiplies. 1:1:N:N compounds."</div>
        <div class="canon-line">"Campaigns reset. Infrastructure compounds."</div>
        <div class="canon-line">"The strongest advocacy doesn't need to be asked for. It needs to be worth doing."</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- AUTHOR -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">&bull;</span> Author
    </div>
    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
      <strong>Roy</strong> - <a href="https://twitter.com/doubts" style="color: var(--accent);">@doubts</a>
    </p>
    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
      Founder at <a href="https://wozku.com" style="color: var(--accent);">Wozku</a> - the first platform built for ALG teams.
    </p>
    <p class="t-label" style="margin-top: var(--sp-4);">Coined 2024 &middot; Framework v0.2 &middot; advocacyled.com</p>
  </div>

</Base>
